headline.main: RUSSIA, YUGOSLAVIA UNEASY OVER REICH; Moscow Said to Have Declared State of Siege in Odessa -- More Nazi Troops in Austria PHILOFF TRIP IS WATCHED Bulgarian Premier's Visit to Vienna Is Believed Certain to Involve German Plans

lead_paragraph: BERNE. Switzerland, Jan. 2 -- After having temporarily died down over the holidays, reports are once again beginning to reach informed diplomatic observers here of further military developments in the Balkans.
abstract: USSR and Yugoslavia reaction to Filoff Vienna visit
